About 60 school children have been rushed to hospital due to suspected food poisoning at a primary school in The Hills in Johannesburg South on Wednesday. Numerous vehicles from ER24 were immediately dispatched to the scene. Upon arrival, ER24 paramedics, along with other services, were immediately lead to the sick child children.The children were assessed and it was found that 20 of them were complaining of abdominal pain as well as nausea and vomiting, spokesperson Russel Meiring said.They were treated and thereafter transported to South Rand and Baragwanath Hospital for urgent care. The children later told paramedics that they had apparently been given sweets by an unknown man the previous day,&#8221; ER24 said.TNA Reporter 